From d4cf8e8301ddffdd1e996386e69ded6cbd7d4b5e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:31 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 20/65] media: rockchip: rkvenc2: free class messages on
 allocation failure

Plain-language impact:
Failed task setup no longer leaks already allocated per-class register buffers.

Kernel details:
The free_task label can be reached after class-message allocation. Call rkvenc_free_class_msg(task) there before kfree(task); the helper is idempotent.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c
index 73ccbeeeb5db..c4cffb7b3a84 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c
@@ -1266,6 +1266,7 @@ static void *rkvenc_alloc_task(struct mpp_session *session,
 	/* free class register buffer */
 	rkvenc_free_class_msg(task);
 free_task:
+	rkvenc_free_class_msg(task);
 	kfree(task);
 
 	return NULL;
-- 
